"a.怕痒的；易怒的 【英】 adj. 怕痒的(sensitive to being tickled);棘手的(difficult) 【考】 pliant : influence / ticklish : offend(顺从的容易被影响/ 不稳定的容易被冒犯)反义词：imperturbab le(冷静的) adj. 怕痒的; 棘手的 【记】源于: tickle(v 胳肢; 使发痒), tick = stick(n 小棍), le乐: 用小棍使你乐－使发痒. 【参】tickler(n 记事本; 使人发痒的人) 【类】pliant: influence = ticklish: offend顺从容易被影响 = 易怒的容易被冒犯 【反】imperturbable(adj 沉着冷静的) 【记】痒痒肉的地方很敏感，需要小心处理 ticklish (adj.)  ""easily tickled,"" 1590s, from tickle + -ish. Literal sense is attested later than the figurative sense ""easy to upset"" (1580s). An earlier word for this was tickly (1520s). Meaning ""difficult to do, dubious, requiring great care"" is from 1590s. Related: Ticklishly; ticklishness."
